The paper discusses the use of Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) for time series forecasting, which is a common topic in the field of Neural Networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the optimization and learning phases of MLP, which are important topics in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a pruning process to improve the forecasting accuracy, which involves selecting inputs and neurons, a task that is related to Feature Selection (cs.SD) and Data Mining (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, and cs.DS.
